==English==

===Noun===
'''truss'''

# A bandage and belt used to hold a hernia in place.
# A framework of beams forming a rigid [[structure]].
# A triangular bracket in architecture.
===Transitive Verb===
'''to truss'''

# To tie up a bird before cooking it.
# To secure or bind with ropes.
# To support.

